dataTypes.description:
total number of vulnerable people within the city (numerator) divided by the city’s total population (denominator).

— persons with physical or mental impairments;
— pregnant women;
— ill or undernourished people;
— the homeless;
— people located in slums and informal housing;
— refugees and internally displaced people;
— transient or nomadic communities.
Other population segments in the city (i.e. children and the elderly) that may be vulnerable to hazards due to location or context-specific factors may also be considered in the interpretation of city population vulnerability.
